CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper July 28, 1945, pg. 10, reads: "Out-of-Towners - Pictured are relatives of Dr. and Mrs. R. W. Dixon of 536 Francis Street. A niece, Miss Margetta Morse, who is a sophomore at Tuskegee Institute; Dr. Dixon's mother, Mrs. H. R. Dixon, instructor at Dunbar High School in Mobile, Ala.; and a sister, Miss Helen A. Dixon, Red Cross case worker in Chicago. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Dr. R. W. Dixon posed with Margetta Morse, Mrs. Dixon, Mrs. H. R. Dixon, Helen A. Dixon, and dog in Dixon living room, 536 Francis Street, Hill District
